  "prompt": "Is there any way to insert image/picture in nedit text editor?",
  "response": "NEdit (Nirvana Editor) is primarily a text editor and does not natively support direct image insertion like some word processors. However, here are a few alternative approaches you can consider:\n\n1. Text References:\n- You can insert text references or file paths to images\n- Example: [image: /path/to/image.jpg]\n\n2. External Image Viewers:\n- Open images in a separate image viewer while editing text in NEdit\n- Use command-line tools or system image viewers\n\n3. Alternative Text Editors:\n- If image insertion is crucial, consider alternatives like:\n  - gedit\n  - Kate\n  - Visual Studio Code\n  - LibreOffice Writer\n\n4. Markup Languages:\n- Use markup languages that support image references\n  - Markdown: ![alt text](image.jpg)\n  - HTML: <img src=\"image.jpg\">\n\n5. External Tools:\n- Some external tools/scripts can help embed image references\n- Use plugins or custom scripts\n\nWhile NEdit is excellent for text editing, it's not designed for rich media integration. For image-intensive work, consider specialized text editors or word processors.",
